### Render items with Static component in JSX

Source: https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink/blob/master/readme.md

The Static component renders each item in an array using a provided function. The function receives the item and its index. A `key` must be assigned to the root component.

```jsx
<Static items={['a', 'b', 'c']}>
	{(item, index) => {
		// This function is called for every item in ['a', 'b', 'c']
		// `item` is 'a', 'b', 'c'
		// `index` is 0, 1, 2
		return (
			<Box key={index}>
				<Text>Item: {item}</Text>
			</Box>
		);
	}}
</Static>
```

