### Newline Component: Basic Usage (Ink/React)

Source: https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink/blob/master/readme.md

Illustrates how to use the Newline component within Ink applications to insert newline characters. The Newline component must be used within a Text component. The 'count' prop can specify the number of newlines.

```jsx
import {render, Text, Newline} from 'ink';

const Example = () => (
	<Text>
		<Text color="green">Hello</Text>
		<Newline />
		<Text color="red">World</Text>
	</Text>
);

render(<Example />);
```

