### Programmatically Focus Component by ID

Source: https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink/blob/master/readme.md

Shows how to focus a specific component by its ID using the focus(id) method. Accepts a string ID parameter to target a component with matching focus ID. If no component with that ID exists, focuses the next available component.

```javascript
import {useFocusManager, useInput} from 'ink';

const Example = () => {
	const {focus} = useFocusManager();

	useInput(input => {
		if (input === 's') {
			// Focus the component with focus ID 'someId'
			focus('someId');
		}
	});

	return …
};
```

