### Basic Counter Component for CLI Output

Source: https://github.com/vadimdemedes/ink/blob/master/readme.md

Demonstrates a simple Ink component that renders a continuously updating counter. It uses React's useState and useEffect hooks to manage the counter's state and timer. The output is displayed as green text in the terminal.

```jsx
import React, {useState, useEffect} from 'react';
import {render, Text} from 'ink';

const Counter = () => {
	const [counter, setCounter] = useState(0);

	useEffect(() => {
		const timer = setInterval(() => {
			setCounter(previousCounter => previousCounter + 1);
		}, 100);

		return () => {
			clearInterval(timer);
		};
	}, []);

	return <Text color="green">{counter} tests passed</Text>;
};

render(<Counter />);
```

